<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="223" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d223">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72111/505½</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-15">15 <hi rend="smallcaps">October</hi>, 1914</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Lansing</hi>: For fear this should not
                            reach you promptly otherwise, I am sending it to you within a few
                            minutes of its receipt here.<note n="10" xml:id="d223fn1">Note from the
                                British Ambassador to President Wilson, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>The tone of it is so candid and sincere, and so earnest that I am sure
                            you will wish to send our reply at once.</p>
                        <p>Cordially,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>